# Ori♡n Shows — environment variables for local development and testing.
#
# The application itself never reads these: runtime Supabase config is loaded
# from public/config.js (see docs/20-DEPLOYMENT_AND_OPERATIONS.md). These
# variables are only consumed by the Supabase-backed integration and E2E test
# suites (tests/integration/, tests/e2e/*.supabase.spec.ts), which skip
# themselves with a clear message when unset.
#
# Copy this file to .env (git-ignored) and fill in real values, or export the
# same names in your shell/CI before running:
#   npm run test:integration
#   npm run test:e2e
#
# Never put a secret/service-role key here or anywhere in this repository —
# only the publishable/anon key is ever valid for this project (see
# docs/17-SECURITY_AND_PRIVACY.md).

# --- Option A: local Supabase CLI stack (`supabase start`, requires Docker) ---
# `supabase status` prints the exact local URL and anon key after `supabase start`.
SUPABASE_TEST_URL=http://127.0.0.1:54321
SUPABASE_TEST_ANON_KEY=

# --- Option B: a disposable hosted Supabase project dedicated to test runs ---
# Never point these at the production project.
# SUPABASE_TEST_URL=https://your-test-project.supabase.co
# SUPABASE_TEST_ANON_KEY=sb_publishable_...
